3. How to Compile/Run SPIMS: 
=====================================

1) Build the application using the provided Makefile using the 'make'
   command. The executable will be found in the bin directory
2) The SPIMS application can be ran using any one of the following commands:

   './spims -p <pattern_image> -s <source_image>'
   './spims -pdir <pattern_image_dir> -s <source_image>'
   './spims -p <pattern_image> -sdir <source_image_dir>'
   './spims -pdir <pattern_image_dir> -sdir <source_image_dir>'

3) If a match is found it will be returned in the format specified in the
   assignment:

   '<file1> matches <file2> at <m1>x<n1>+<x>+<y>'.

   If a match is not found program will exit with exit code 0.
   If the inputs were unacceptable the program will exit with exit code 1

